As the earth apparently shook under the feet of Lowvelders this morning, social media was set abuzz as residents tried to investigate the possibility of an earthquake. Though many didn&#8217;t feel a thing, a few agreed that they definitely did. Lowvelder consulted a reliable source, who confirmed that no earthquake was recorded in the Lowveld this morning. However, he did not rule out the possibility of a surface tremor, which is not the same as an earthquake but still causes a tremor.He explained that if lightning strikes an area that is less dense than others, or if a series of bolts hit the earth, it can possibly cause a surface tremor which can be felt from miles away.Read the latest update on the weather